<!-- 1. In jQuery terminology, what is the difference between the “jQuery function”
and the “jQuery object”?
- jQuery function is the entry point to the jQuery library and is responsible for selecting elements
- jQuery object represents a collection of elements and provides methods for manipulation and interaction with those elements. -->


<!-- 2. Write jQuery code to find all h1 elements that are
children of a div element and make their background color red. Sample HTML: -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.6.4/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script>
      $(document).ready(function () {
        $("div").find("h1").css("background-color", "red");
      });
    </script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>abc</h1>
    <br />
    <div>
      <h1>div-1</h1>
      <h1>div-2</h1>
    </div>
    <h1>xyz</h1>
  </body>
</html>

<!-- 3. Use a jQuery method to insert the text "YES!" at the end of the <p> element. -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.6.4/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script>
      // <!—INSERT YOUR JQUERY CODE HERE - - >
      $(document).ready(function () {
        $("p").append("YES!");
      });
    </script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>Is jQuery FUN or what?</p>
  </body>
</html>
